  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides arguments for creating a customized typeface instance.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that collects the arguments used to create a customized version of a typeface via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It lets you specify a font collection index, a color palette, palette color overrides, and variable font axis coordinates — all in one place.

Because it is a `ref struct`, `SKFontArguments` can only be used on the stack and cannot be stored in fields or used as a generic type argument.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
    },
};

using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("MyFont.ttf");
using var customTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
